"", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112273/chrome-native-windows-on-arm-qualcomm-snapdragon", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "A native version of Chrome arrives for Arm-based Windows PCs", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Chrome logo surrounded by yellow circles\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bLcy6Jl-ZEeCouXu2nzyq3tgrfI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233989/STK114_Google_Chrome_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WaNdps\">Google is releasing an optimized version of its Chrome browser for Windows on Arm this week, the search giant has announced alongside chipmaker Qualcomm. The official release comes two months after an early version of the browser was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/26/24051485/google-chrome-windows-arm-support-canary-channel-test\">spotted in Chrome\u2019s Canary channel</a>. Qualcomm says the release \u201cwill roll out starting today.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"Z2kQkk\">The release will be a big deal for any Chrome users with Windows machines powered by Arm-based processors, who\u2019ll now have access to a much faster native browser. That\u2019s in contrast to t", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T16:00:00+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24112407/princess-peach-showtime-review-nintendo-switch", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Princess Peach: Showtime! is clever and playful, but Peach deserves more", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Princess Peach: Showtime! featuring Princess Peach in an ice blue figure skating leotard skating, extending her arms out wide with a joyous expression on her face.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Dp6HB-VobIaPffcBnZmRLLtgyR0=/300x0:1920x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233988/PrincessPeachShowtime_FigureSkater1_png_jpgcopy.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Delightful design and the beloved royal badass isn\u2019t enough to save Peach\u2019s first game in 19 years from being a touch boring.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24112407/princess-peach-showtime-review-nintendo-switch\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T15:34:56+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112369/riaa-2023-music-revenue-streaming-vinyl-cds-physical-media", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Vinyl records outsell CDs for the second year running", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A three-year bar chart showing Vinyl topping physical media growth.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BAt51AHy78I2ZG3v1Z8ZmeOaUVo=/280x0:1138x572/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233914/2023_Year_End_Socials_031224a7.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Vinyl reigns when it comes to physical media.\ufeff</em> | Image: RIAA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qeAQTe\">People bought 43 million vinyl records last year, <a href=\"https://www.riaa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2023-Year-End-Revenue-Statistics.pdf\">according to the Recording Industry Association of America</a> (RIAA). That\u2019s 6 million more than the number of CDs sold in 2023, marking the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/10/23633605/vinyl-records-surpasses-cd-music-sales-us-riaa\">second time since 1987</a> that\u2019s happened and reflecting the steady 17-year-running growth of vinyl sales. </p>\n<p id=\"NXRtUj\">Vinyl, which tends to be pricier than the newer format, also f", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T15:20:27+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112341/drought-heatwave-hydropower-western-us-low", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Heat and drought are sucking US hydropower dry", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A half-empty water reservoir, with a pale layer of rocks above the waterline showing how high the water used to be.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QDDoNhBy8RVrTo6oH_G4mDzHxt8=/0x0:5760x3840/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233865/1621377566.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Lake Mead, formed by Hoover Dam on the Colorado River in the Southwestern United States, at 47 percent capacity as viewed on August 14, 2023 near Boulder City, Nevada.</em> | Photo by George Rose/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"v4Ed78\">The amount of hydropower generated in the Western US last year was the lowest it\u2019s been in more than two decades. Hydropower generation in the region fell by 11 percent during the 2022\u20132023 water year compared to the year prior, according to <a href=\"https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=61645\">preliminary data</a> from the Energy Information Administration\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.eia.gov/electri", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T14:30:00+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112285/microsoft-teams-copilot-ai-features-improvements", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Microsoft Teams is getting smarter Copilot AI features", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Microsoft Teams illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SD6Ep0OVy43CctFDttFz9aGdiWs=/0x0:2640x1760/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233730/microsoftteams.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"V9dxMI\">Microsoft is improving the way its AI-powered Copilot works in Microsoft Teams with new ways to invoke the assistant during meeting chats, summaries, and more. </p>\n<p id=\"TBYSsE\">Copilot is already able to summarize Teams meetings, but in the coming months, it will combine spoken transcripts and written chats into a single view to make it easier to catch up on meetings you might have missed.</p>\n<p id=\"vOpesm\">Copilot in Teams is also getting improvements to composing messages in chat, allowing Teams users to rewrite a message in new ways. \u201cCopilot can adjust your message to add a call to action, or like how a pirate would speak,\u201d says <a href=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.c", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T14:00:00+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24111687/dragons-dogma-2-review-xbox-ps5-pc", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Dragon\u2019s Dogma 2\u2019s lovable pawns make it an adventure worth fighting for", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of a dragon in the video game Dragon\u2019s Dogma 2.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WL3Y7el3aMXFAnjodA3xsPlwUM4=/394x0:3634x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233630/DD2_Dragon_03_png_jpgcopy.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Capcom</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The sequel to Capcom\u2019s action RPG is big and chaotic, but the companion characters are what make it all work.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24111687/dragons-dogma-2-review-xbox-ps5-pc\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T13:13:03+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24111796/anc-headphones-noise-canceling-clicks-keyboard-iphone-vergecast-podcast", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "AI headphones and clicky phone keys", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of headphones with a motherboard, on top of a Vergecast illustration.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ojMBOzZWBN8kc-AKptYVsKgxzKg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233500/VST_0326_site_v2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge / Photo courtesy of University of Washington</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"INlFwJ\">The world is a noisy place. High-end headphones are getting better at shutting it out; solid noise-canceling headphones from Sony, Bose, and others are increasingly a must-have for anyone who spends a lot of time on planes and trains, or in coffee shops full of people pitching AI startups. It\u2019s a sanity thing, really.</p>\n<p id=\"qX4W0W\">But there are already people working on a giant leap in active noise cancellation. Instead of just blocking all the sound around you, the next generation of headphones might block all the sound you don\u2019t want \u2014 but let in all the things you do want to ", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T12:54:15+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112300/disney-plus-new-logo-hulu-green-teal", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Disney Plus has a new Hulu-ified logo", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/lowT95d_t7nI7VnisReNjBi1wCE=/0x10:1920x1290/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233411/Disney_logo_update_hed.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The old Disney Plus icon logo (left) compared with the updated teal one (right).</em> | Image: Disney</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aoXoiA\">Disney has made some slight but notable updates to the logo and splash screen for its Disney Plus streaming service that likely nod to its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/6/23990787/disney-plus-hulu-one-app-experience-beta-launch\">looming merger with Hulu</a>. The biggest change is the new teal / seafoam background color, which appears to be a rough mix between its original blue background and the green that Hulu uses.</p>\n<p id=\"tDd3qn\">At face value alone, the updated design \u2014 which can already be seen on the Disney Plus website and various app stores \u2014 makes sense for the corporate giant. Aside fr", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T12:34:11+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112309/sony-ps5-community-game-help", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "The PS5 is getting an automatic game clip feature that helps other players", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Sony\u2019s PS5 console.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wlDvmAWRYQni4gwtXrnMwhudER4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233403/vpavic_4278_20201030_0292.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xGXbj9\">Sony is introducing a new Community Game Help feature on the PS5 later this year that is designed to automatically create clips that can help other players. PS5 players will be able to automatically upload gameplay to help contribute to hint videos provided by game developers.</p>\n<p id=\"mYlp6q\">The opt-in experience will let your PS5 automatically capture a game clip when you complete an activity in supported titles. \u201cThen, it will be reviewed by a moderator, and if approved, your video will be published as a Game Help hint for PlayStation players to watch, learn from, and rate,\u201d <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/03/26/introducing-community-game-help", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T12:00:00+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24111326/ai-search-perplexity-copilot-you-google-review", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Here\u2019s why AI search engines really can\u2019t kill Google", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of a chatbot swinging into a Google logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HJXKqKbqTjDSaZz3Drs_d3gNqhE=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233337/IMG_4450.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Vincent Kilbride</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The AI search tools are getting better \u2014 but they don\u2019t yet understand what a search engine really is and how we really use them.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24111326/ai-search-perplexity-copilot-you-google-review\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T10:34:33+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112277/canva-affinity-acquisition-design-software-suite-adobe-rival", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Canva acquires Affinity to fill the Adobe-sized holes in its design suite", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Canva and Affinity logos on white background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Zd0tMJQkHsAFlfnzMa-Lc8Si7dM=/0x94:2568x1806/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73233235/Canva_affinity_banner_2.31c4b05d.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Affinity\u2019s professional design software could give Canva the edge it needs to seriously compete against Adobe.</em> | Image: Canva</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"99Fs0f\">Web-based design platform Canva has acquired the <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Faffinity.serif.com%2Fen-us%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F3%2F26%2F24112277%2Fcanva-affinity-acquisition-design-software-suite-adobe-rival\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Affinity creative software suite</a>, positioning itself as a challenger to Adobe\u2019s grip over the digital design industry. Canva <a href=\"https://go.redirect", "vote": 0, "artist": null}, {"manual_status_code": 0, "date_published": "2024-03-26T01:07:49+00:00", "album": "", "page_rating_contents": 94, "comments": [], "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "language": "en", "page_rating": 94, "user": null, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "status_code": 0, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/25/24111963/nissan-ev-plan-2026-solid-state-batteries", "thumbnail": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "title": "Nissan announces plans to make 16 new electrified vehicles by 2026", "age": null, "permanent": false, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Nissan\u2019s Ariya electric SUV with gold paint\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0-iSc4rrvgWBujk0sIWOlhu-_-0=/258x0:5231x3315/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73232771/2023_Nissan_Ariya_US_44.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nissan</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kQVTOj\">Nissan has <a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20240325809457/en/Nissan-Launches-The-Arc-Business-Plan-to-Drive-Value-and-Enhance-Competitiveness-and-Profitability/?feedref=JjAwJuNHiystnCoBq_hl-Q-tiwWZwkcswR1UZtV7eGe24xL9TZOyQUMS3J72mJlQ7fxFuNFTHSunhvli30RlBNXya2izy9YOgHlBiZQk2LOzmn6JePCpHPCiYGaEx4DL1Rq8pNwkf3AarimpDzQGuQ%3D%3D\">laid out a new plan</a> to electrify 16 of the 30 vehicles it produces by 2026, with the rest using internal combustion instead. For those of us in North America, the company says it plans to release seven new vehicles in the US and Canada, although it\u2019s not clear how many of those will be some type of EV.</p>\n<p id=\"5K", "vote": 0, "artist": null}]